y of policy borrowing under new conditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aLanguage and languagesxGlobalization. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aLanguage policyxEurope. 0aLanguage policyzEurope. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh  aCEFR.  aEuropean Union.  alanguage education.  alanguage policy.1 aByram, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aParmenter, Lynne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769731840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847697318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847697318/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK